SIMPLE: unknow
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unknow
<hw>Un*know"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>know</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To cease to know; to lose the knowledge of.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fail of knowing; to be ignorant of.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unknow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unknow
<hw>Un*know"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <ets>Un-</ets> not,
<er>Know</er>.]</ety> <def>Unknown.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧French of Paris was to her <xex>unknow</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unknowledged</ent>⟦br⟧
